Sherry said Friday that when band members parted ways four years ago, they left the door open to performing together again at some point. He said that fans at his recent shows, in Maine and around the country, often ask when The Ghost of Paul Revere might play together again. Now he can tell them.

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/Newyear2_c7ef7b.jpg?w=250&h=250&crop=1)](https://www.pressherald.com/2022/04/19/after-11-year-ride-portland-band-the-ghost-of-paul-revere-is-breaking-up/)

