“I think we all needed some space from it for a while,” said Sherry, who lives in Litchfield. “We got the instruments out together just the other day, and played together for the first time in four years.”

Sherry said the band’s plan is to play only the two September shows. Presale begins Tuesday on [the band’s website](https://www.ghostofpaulrevere.com/?utm_source=ig&utm_medium=social&utm_content=link_in_bio&fbclid=PAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQMMjU2MjgxMDQwNTU4AAGn2Tln9JbKaTyigR5eosrHDJxm_MArWIfnPM_gcEyNeo5VlLBa1tKOjBQH_aE_aem_RfRXzfeSNXJt16yQLjPiUA) and tickets will go on sale to the general public Jan. 23. The lineup of other bands for the Ghostland festival will also be announced Tuesday, Sherry said.

