Sherry said the band picked the new Live at Madrid’s to be part of its reunion weekend at least partly to play a new Portland venue. They also have worked with and are friendly with several of the people involved in the new space, including talent buyer Meg Shorette, owner Josh Schlesinger and local musician Cam Jones, who is handling marketing.

[Live at Madrid’s](https://www.instagram.com/liveatmadrids/) is slated to open in mid-March and no other shows have yet been announced for the venue. Schlesinger says he envisions the space filling a gap in Portland’s music scene: a mid-sized place for bands to play before playing the larger venues in the city, like the 1,900-seat State Theatre.

